Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

Once boiled, pour the @Water{50%ml} into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high
heat. Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain, pop
back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} (no oil) on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince
as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT:
Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the
middle. While the beef cooks, open the remaining sachets.

Add the @Peri Peri Seasoning{2%sachets}, @Tomato Passata{1%carton},
@Mixed Beans{1%carton}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and water (see pantry for both) to the
beef. Cook, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and stir through the @Smoky Base Paste{1%sachet} and
@Butter{20%g} (see pantry). Taste and season with salt and pepper. Add a splash
of water if it's too thick.

Share rice between #serving bowls{}.

Top with the smoky peri peri beef and sprinkle over the cheese.

Enjoy!

> Ready in just 15 minutes, this Super Quick Smoky Beef Peri Peri Rice Bowl is
> smoky and spicy with a slightly sweet kick. Peri peri contains smoked paprika,
> ancho chilli powder, ground cumin and oregano.